abstract: There’s a problem with tech companies using dual-class stock schemes: They can work well until they do not.

lead_paragraph: “Presidents are not kings,” wrote Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson of the Federal District Court for the District of Columbia this week, in a 120-page decision in the ongoing fight between President Trump and the House Democrats over whether current and former senior White House officials must comply with congressional subpoenas in the impeachment inquiry.

lead_paragraph: At Thanksgiving, many of us will be subject to — or subjecting our hosts to — a wide range of opinions about the impeachment inquiry. abstract: Dating back to “The Apprentice,” he has long grasped that cultural loyalties can animate Americans far more than high-minded principles.
snippet: Dating back to “The Apprentice,” he has long grasped that cultural loyalties can animate Americans far more than high-minded principles.
lead_paragraph: Much like the way rearview mirrors bend space-time so that the objects you’ve sped away from still remain “closer than they appear,” there was a time not too long ago — although it doesn’t always seem like it — when Donald Trump seemed like harmless fun to most of us. For me, that was about 15 years ago, when “The Apprentice” debuted in prime time on NBC.

snippet: Or society, for that matter. How did this preposterous idea leap to the forefront of conservative thinking?
lead_paragraph: When Attorney General William Barr warned in a speech at Notre Dame on Oct. 11 that secular liberalism had unleashed “licentiousness — the unbridled pursuit of personal appetites at the expense of the common good,” there was a glaring incongruity.

headline_main: Texas, Thanksgiving, Duke: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: Two years after Hurricanes Maria and Irma, records show the agency’s work on long-term recovery on the islands is crawling compared with some states on the mainland.
snippet: Two years after Hurricanes Maria and Irma, records show the agency’s work on long-term recovery on the islands is crawling compared with some states on the mainland.
lead_paragraph: ST. CROIX, U.S. Virgin Islands — More than two years after back-to-back hurricanes ravaged this tropical island, medical workers are still treating gunshot wounds in hallways and kidney failure in a trailer. They ignore their own inflamed rashes that they say are caused by the mold that has shut down an entire hospital floor below a still-porous roof.

abstract: In 1981, he was elected mayor of Burlington. But the city’s bureaucracy showed him that winning wasn’t everything. So he learned how to fight back.
snippet: In 1981, he was elected mayor of Burlington. But the city’s bureaucracy showed him that winning wasn’t everything. So he learned how to fight back.
lead_paragraph: BURLINGTON, Vt. — The young woman on the political leaflet was smiling, but the message printed beside her in bold capital letters was severe. “The last two years,” it said, “have shown that those who made the revolution are not always the best to lead after the coup.”

abstract: As fights over the president’s stonewalling of Congress play out slowly in courts, he is reducing the prospect that voters learn new damaging facts about him before the 2020 election.
snippet: As fights over the president’s stonewalling of Congress play out slowly in courts, he is reducing the prospect that voters learn new damaging facts about him before the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Critics of President Trump cheered on Monday when a federal judge ruled that the former White House counsel Donald F. McGahn II must testify to Congress — and scathingly labeled “fiction” the administration’s arguments that top White House aides are immune from congressional subpoenas.
